  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Architectural Coordinator",
  "description": "<h3><strong>Roles &amp; Responsibilities:</strong></h3>\n<ul>\n  <li>Oversee and coordinate <strong>architectural works</strong> to ensure they align with the project schedule, design, and specifications.</li>\n  <li>Review architectural drawings, specifications, and shop drawings to ensure compliance with the design intent and building codes.</li>\n  <li>Monitor the execution of architectural work on-site, ensuring quality, safety, and compliance with specifications.</li>\n  <li>Liaise with architects, contractors, consultants, and other stakeholders to resolve design issues and ensure smooth project execution.</li>\n  <li>Ensure that all architectural work complies with relevant local regulations, building codes, and safety standards.</li>\n  <li>Maintain accurate project records, including drawings, design changes, site inspections, and progress reports.</li>\n  <li>Identify and address design or construction challenges, ensuring that they are resolved promptly to avoid project delays.</li>\n  <li>Monitor the quality of materials and workmanship to meet project requirements and standards.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3><strong>Job Requirements:</strong></h3>\n<ul>\n  <li>Bachelor's Degree or Diploma in Architecture.</li>\n  <li>Minimum <strong>5 years</strong> of experience in architectural coordination for construction projects.</li>\n  <li>Strong knowledge of architectural design principles, building codes, and construction methods.</li>\n  <li>Proficiency in using AutoCAD, Revit, or other architectural software.</li>\n  <li>Ability to read and interpret architectural drawings and specifications.</li>\n  <li>Strong communication, organizational, and problem-solving skills.</li>\n  <li>Familiarity with local building regulations and industry standards.</li>\n  <li>Experience in coordinating with different stakeholders, including architects, contractors, and consultants.</li>\n</ul>",
